Euro Extends Decline After Trichet Says ‘Downside Risks’ Have Intensified

-- B y   D a n i e l   T i l l e s
-- 
2011-09-08T12:36:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/euro-extends-decline-after-trichet-says-downside-risks-have-intensified.html
The euro extended declines against
the dollar after European Central Bank President Jean-Claude
Trichet said “downside risks” to the region have intensified.  The 17-nation currency weakened 0.6 percent to $1.4018 as
of 1:35 p.m. in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daniel Tilles in London at 
